A template/tutorial for how to get (and refresh) a cookie with selenium in python, so a script can make calls to a public API through requestsA template/tutorial for how to get (and refresh) a cookie with selenium in python, so a script can make calls to a public API through requests

Why? - It's ideal to not scrape a front end and instead intercept API requests. For this, you usually need cookies to trick the server into thinking you've actually been on the site.

Can't I just scrape this? - Yeah, but it's slower and less reliable.

Uses Poetry for env and package management!
